# db/.gitignore — gitignore rules for the db image build context.
#
# The db image is built from this directory (Dockerfile + init/01-content.sql).
# Everything that's bake output (regenerated on every `bake_image.sh` run)
# lives here; cross-project concerns (Python __pycache__, IDE dirs, OS junk,
# secrets, ...) stay in the root .gitignore so they apply uniformly.

# Bake output — pg_dump'd SQL, regenerated every time bake_image.sh runs.
# Keeping it out of the repo (and out of the diff) means we don't bloat git
# history with multi-MB SQL blobs that change on every content update.
init/01-content.sql

# No longer used (audio moved to COS in this release). Kept here as a guard
# rail in case future bake work reintroduces local audio.
seed/
